:: Aidan_Hoxea {"position":"1000,1875","size":"100,100"}
He smiles as if he was recollecting memories and responds to you by saying that when he was driven from his duchy and forced into exile he met with his former companions and allies many are different races. Deciding not to remain in the Rokian Empire, Captain Ottile suggested they sail southwesr towards the unknown, hoping to find a new land where they could lay low. They soon found the island Hoxea, a large island filed with resources ranging from lumber to ores and gemstones. When they settled they all agreed too not discriminate based on religion and culture.

Deciding to continue the conversation you ask about...

[[His sisters and possibly their motives|Aidan_sister]]
[[His time as a mercenary|Aidan_merc]]


:: Aidan_claims {"position":"850,2025","size":"100,100"}
Prince Aidan thinks for a moment before he looks back to you saying that, he has no intention of coming back to the Duchy of Diamond Bay to rule as a duke of an empire that is plagued by internal conflicts. Howeever he states that he will return to the duchy not to rule but for answers as to why his sisters had deposed him as he doesn't want theories but rather answers.

Deciding to continue the conversation you ask about...

[[Why Hoxea is more diverse and more tolerant than other nations|Aidan_Hoxea]]


:: Aidan_lore {"position":"975,1700","size":"100,100"}
Prince Aidan looks annoyed at first before he says that he was originally a duke in the Rokian Empire before he was ousted from his seat at Diamond Point by his three sisters. He looks a bit saddened after mentioning his sisters he continues further that he doesn't know why his sisters ousted him.

Deciding to know more you ask about...

[[His sisters and possibly their motives|Aidan_sister]]
[[Why Hoxea is more diverse and more tolerant than other nations|Aidan_Hoxea]]


:: Aidan_merc {"position":"975,2050","size":"100,100"}
Prince Aidan laughs and explains that when he was fifteen years old under preassure from his father he was sent to the far north in Mica county to meet Count Morris the Seventh, an old friend of his father to be further educated in the ways of war as his father saw his potential in war. Once he arrived in Duravich the seat of the Counts of Mica he was greeted warmly and trained under the Count of Mica and even participated in the Seventh Rokian-Sernian war. His face soon lost the smile and said that during the Battle of Vetenets Fields, We we're ambushed by some Zra orcs the Sernians had hired the orcs served as a shock unit and soon surrounded by Sernian footmen in the front and cavalry in the rear Count Morris was wounded and I rallied the men to make a mad charge to kill their leader, Sir Mark of Blacksand. The charge worked we killed Sir Mark and routed the enemy but at a heavy cost.

Deciding not to be awkward you ask the Prince to...

[[Continue the story|Aidan_merc2]]


:: Aidan_merc2 {"position":"1175,1900","size":"100,100"}
The prince looked at you for a moment before breaking the silence, he continued his story, After the war I joined many different mercenary companies and fought with many leaders. Many of the mercenary companies he once fought with joined his court here in Askby, becoming the first inhabitants of Hoxea. He points to one of the guards  saying that one is a Rethian a highlander to be precise. This caught you off guard as what you've heard from travelers Rethians are loyal to their own race so to see one standing guard for a Ronian duke now prince was impressive to say the least.

Thinking about his story you...

[[Thank the prince for his time and excuse yourself|
[[Ask who joined the Prince's court|Aidan_relations]]


