:: Askby crim {"position":"400,1025","size":"100,100"}
Hess further elucidates on the origins of the principality's prosperity, recounting the pivotal role played by the gold Aidan secured when he narrowly escaped betrayal. Instead of hoarding it for personal gain, Aidan invested the gold wisely, channeling it into infrastructure projects such as roads and bolstering local healthcare services. This strategic allocation significantly improved the living standards of the families of mercenaries who chose to follow Aidan, eradicating the need for banditry as a means of survival.

Moreover, Aidan's decisive action in quelling an infamous pirate threat five years ago resonates in the collective memory of the region. The resounding defeat inflicted upon the great pirate fleet sent shockwaves through the maritime underworld, dissuading many pirates from venturing into Hoxea's waters out of fear of reprisal.

While murmurs regarding the taxes levied by Aidan persist among peasants and merchants, there's a prevailing acknowledgment that the taxation serves a noble cause. Aidan's court ensures that the majority of tax revenue is reinvested into the principality, increasing the quality of life for its citizens through various developmental initiatives. Consequently, while some may grumble, few can dispute that Aidan's leadership primarily aims to enrich the lives of his people rather than lining his own pockets.

[[Thank the guild master for his time and leave|Askby]]


:: Askby guild {"position":"500,1150","size":"100,100"}
You soon find the guild master for Askby, a man appearing to be in his early sixties, clad in attire befitting a seasoned merchant who has traversed many trade routes. Introducing himself as Hess, the guild master provides an insight into the economic landscape of the Principality of Hoxea.

Hess elaborates on the principality's economic stronghold, centered around Askby, the largest and sole city, serving as both the economic hub and the capital. The region is fortified with small forts strategically positioned along the roads and coastlines, while quaint villages speckle the surrounding areas. Notably, a substantial underground citadel within Mt. Cyra serves as a bastion for storage and refuge in times of external threat, a testament to the principality's preparedness.

Curious about potential trade opportunities, you inquire about goods in demand within the Principality. Hess explains that, owing to the reforms instituted by Prince Aidan during the principality's inception, Hoxea has achieved a remarkable degree of self-sufficiency. The fertile lands yield plentiful agricultural produce, supplemented by the cultivation facilitated by greenhouses. Additionally, the abundant mineral and gem deposits within Mt. Cyra fuel trade ventures, attracting skilled artisans from across the realm.

However, Hess reveals the need for exotic goods, expressing a willingness to pay a premium for rarities such as ivory, pearls, Brilscales, and other coveted commodities, which would enrich the principality's trade.

Wishing to know more about Hoxea you ask..

[[How are bandits and pirates in the area?|Askby crim]]
[[Thank the guild master for his time and leave|Askby]]



