:: Askby vil1 {"position":"1425,1000","size":"100,100"}
The large farming settlement of Krasna,  marked on local maps, stands as a breadbasket Hoxea. As you approach, the sheer scale of the settlement becomes apparent. Vast orchards brimming with fruit trees and glass houses sheltering diverse crops dot the landscape, testament to the settlement’s agricultural prowess.

On the rolling hills, oxen and their handlers plow the fields, preparing the fertile earth for planting. Higher up, on the steeper slopes, industrious Biram Dwarves carve terraces into the hillsides, maximizing the available land for cultivation. Nearby, you notice mages employing their skills to freeze freshly harvested goods, preserving them for longer journeys and ensuring a steady supply of fresh produce for distant markets.

As you draw closer to Krasna, the presence of a well-armed military force becomes evident. Soldiers clad in more elaborate armor than traditional guards patrol the area, their imposing polearms gleaming in the sunlight. Archers stand ready with bows, their watchful eyes scanning the horizon. Mounted soldiers, equipped with lighter armor and armed with spears, ride across the fields, prepared to swiftly engage any threats. This formidable force is clearly tasked with safeguarding Hoxea’s breadbasket and the surrounding isles, ensuring the continued flow of essential resources.

Entering the heart of Krasna, the settlement transitions into a vibrant small town. The air is filled with the rich, comforting scents of agriculture and food production. You see residents drying fruits and vegetables, millers diligently turning grains into flour, and bakers crafting loaves of bread and delicious pies. People are busy sugaring fruits to preserve them, transforming them into sweet jellies, and pickling vegetables for longer shelf life. Stalls and shops display an array of preserved goods, ready for trade and consumption.

Amidst this bustling activity, vendors offer a variety of locally produced alcoholic beverages. Beer, wine, and mead made from the honey of local bees are prominently featured, showcasing the region’s diverse and rich culinary traditions. The settlement of Krasna is not just a center of agricultural production; it is a thriving community where the fruits of the land are transformed into a myriad of products that sustain and delight the people of Hoxea.

