:: Sernia_lore {"position":"450,1600","size":"100,100"}
Taylor leads you towards the history section of the library and he pulls out a book titled
"Sernian history and the union of crowns" he states that this is the most detailed book they have and states that he has to go back to the counter to help. As he walks away you begin reading about the recent history of the United Kingdoms of Sernia.

The United Kingdoms of Sernia was formed only a hundred years ago as a union between the Venuiti Kingdom and Kingdom of Rhzi, though not without difficulty as the Kingdom of Rhzi deposed Karl III in favor of his sister Lora I who was married to the king of Venuiti Kingdom Anton IV and formed a union of kingdoms. They have recently annexed the Kosut Marches to the north and as such there is a bit of turmoil. You continue to read and find out that due to succession problems as well as the question of the strength of the monarch multiple rebellions are in progress. Some are Royalists wishing to keep the status quo, some are Loyalists to Jakob I grandson to Karl III who wishes to reclaim the Rhzi Kingdom but nothing more, some are Republicans who wish to dissolve  the Kingdoms in favor of multiple republics bound by a confederation. You also read that a popular religious movement is sweeping the southern part of the kingdoms wish to establish a religious state. The greatest threat was maybe the Kosut seperatists, they have allied with Jakob I as Jakob wishes to reclaim his kingdom in return he promised to make the Kosut Marches independent some have rallied to his cause others fight it while a small few fight for the royalists. Due to the recent instability mercenaries are flooding in for work some nations sent volunteers to their chosen side and even sent supplies or offered refugee. Finishing the book you also deduce that due to the chaos demons and monsters are likely to spawn from it all.

[[You close the book and return to the front desk|Askby Library]]


