:: Training-Askby {"position":"1475,1325","size":"100,100"}
Making your way to the training grounds, you observe soldiers sparring with a variety of weapons: swords, spears, glaives, and halberds. Nearby, others are practicing their marksmanship with bows, javelins, slings, crossbows, and even the rare Hoxan Rifle—known to most outside the principality as an arquebus. Some of the light infantry are also seen throwing small darts at targets.

You notice some soldiers using the Portu Launce, a hand cannon capable of launching small solid balls or some fused to explode. Additionally, some are carrying glass and clay spheres with ropes attached. These spheres are either thrown by hand, launched farther using slings, or shot over great distances with a modified Portu Launce called a Portu Mort.

You also notice soldiers training with larger siege weapons such as cannons, mortars, catapults, scorpions, ballistae, and trebuchets. Engineers on the sidelines take meticulous notes, likely working on ways to improve the efficiency of these formidable machines. Beside them are sappers training to breach walls and fortifications during assaults.

You soon hear horses and spot some knights practicing cavalry skills using lances and longswords, some even practicing skirmish tactics with bows, crossbows, and the new Pistol a smaller black powder weapon. Despite their age, chariots are still fielded. Among the horses, you notice some soldiers riding elephants, wielding long spears and bows, some even using the feared Zubri Crossbow, said to shoot five bolts in ten seconds. Others attempt to ride camels, equipped with lighter armor and spears.

You also spot a smaller cadre of soldiers using a strange device with a tube and a cone connected to a small container on top. From what you see, when a soldier squeezes the trigger, the cone blasts fire. Not wanting to be burned, you continue to move forward.

Amid the activity, you spot Captain Alice. She approaches and, recognizing you, says, "Feel free to use the empty field over there to train your skills." She points to a vacant area, giving you a nod of approval.

