:: Zernia Race {"position":"625,1375","size":"100,100"}
Flipping to the next page you continue to read the history of these races and cultures.

Leplaka: Guardians of the Isles

In the azure waters of the Karlan-Midrin Isles, the Leplaka stand as bastions against the tide of invaders. Once masters of these lands, they now cling to the southern isles and the Great Kran, their resistance unyielding against colonization and conquest. Painted warriors, they blend with the land itself, striking with the fury of a tempest, their resolve bolstered by the icy touch of the Goddess of Frost.

Ronian and Rokian Empires: A Legacy of Glory and Ambition

Eight centuries past, the Ronian Empire cast its shadow over eastern Diventi, only to succumb to internal strife and overextension, crumbling in a blaze of glory. Rising from its ashes, the Rokian Empire sought to reclaim its predecessor's glory, but memories of the old empire linger among the long-lived Biram and the independent United Kingdom of Sernia, symbolized by the revered griffins of the Northern Ronians.

Biram and Rarnul: Guardians of Mountain and Silk

Amidst the eastern mountains dwell the industrious Biram, renowned for their mining prowess and brewing expertise. Divided along clan and tribe lines, they pledge allegiance to the High King of Dwornia, chosen by a spirited contest of libations. In stark contrast, the Rarnul of the south, with their spider-like features, once inhabited the southeastern provinces of the Rokian Empire. Hunted and persecuted for their differences, many seek refuge in distant lands, their plight a testament to the cruelty of imperial rule.

Venuit and Lynar: Keepers of the Rivers and Forests

To the east, the Venuit ply the rivers in their sturdy canoes, mastering the art of water magic and thriving off the bounty of the land. In the southeastern reaches, the reclusive Lynar stand sentinel over the verdant forests, skilled in archery and herbal medicine. Despite occasional clashes with the Biram, they remain staunch defenders of their woodland domain, aided by mystical creatures of the forest.

Kosut Giants and Turthian Traders: Titans and Tastemakers

In the shadow of the mountains, the colossal Kosut giants and their smaller Uti brethren march to battle, wielding enchanted bows and serving as living bulwarks against their foes. Across the plains, the Turthians cultivate spices and trade exotic goods, renowned for their culinary prowess and mastery of falconry. Their lords, astride mighty elephants, wield both power and influence in the courts of Diventi.

Yinto Sorcerers and Zra Orcs: Masters of Magic and Ferocity

Amidst the arcane spires of the Yinto capital, sorcery thrives, though those without the gift are relegated to a lesser status. Yet, all serve in the defense of their realm, trading porcelain and natural goods with distant lands. In the rugged mountains, the Zra orcs, born from violence and isolation, forge crude armor from scraps and looted goods. Though crude in craftsmanship, their skill in smelting is unmatched, a testament to their indomitable spirit in the face of adversity.

